<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>Saint Anthony’s fire • Saint Elmo’s fire</xh5><p> <i>Saint Anthony’s fire—</i>an inflammatory disease of the skin caused by alkaloids produced by a fungus that infests rye and wheat: Outbreaks of <u>Saint Anthony’s Fire</u> were common in countries where populations subsisted on rye bread.</p><p> <i>Saint Elmo’s fire—</i>a naturally occurring corona discharge from a pointed conducting object, such as a ship’s mast, etc.: Ball lightning and <u>Saint Elmo’s fire</u> are sometimes confused.</p> </entry>
